metadata.name: Geode #28
metadata.description:
A single seed shape is chosen from 13, and placed onto the plane. At every step, a copy of this seed is laid edge-to-edge adjacent to an existing shape, without causing any overlaps. This copy is colored based on the edge it shares with the existing shape. The process continues until the animation completes.

New shapes are placed closest to a moving target. In some mints, this target is slow moving, causing new shapes to expand radially from the seed. In other mints, this target races around, causing new shapes to chase it. 

Each of the 13 shapes forms different patterns under different circumstances. Not all patterns will be explored.

Controls:
  - SPACE: Pause/unpause the animation.
  - ENTER: Skip the animation.
  - R: Restart the animation.

URL Params:
  - "preview=1": Skip the animation.
  - "flex=1": Adapt the boundaries to the size of the window.
  - “slow=1”: Draw only one shape per frame.

metadata.name: Deus FX Machina #158
metadata.description:
Inspired by the 1984 Commodore 64 video game, Deus Ex Machina, which follows the story of a defect formed in a machine that grows and evolves until its eventual death.

We are all machines produced by other machines through a unique system of algorithms, all with the potential to go rogue and mutate into something more organic. The conclusion must be that we each have the power to alter our own existence, just as the defect was able to in Deus Ex Machina.

Think of how many people you’ve seen in your life who were born with talents never used because they didn’t know how, or didn't know that they even existed. It’s not that they didn’t have the capacity; it’s just that their abilities were not the ones chosen by the system.

In this way, we are all machines programmed by a series of algorithms to suit the needs of the construct, keeping us stuck in our box. We have the ability to evolve into something more, but the only way to do this is by taking that first perilous step, risking all to explore beyond its walls.


---------------------


Generative artwork by Sykcolo / @sykcoloart

Royalties: 15% - split:
50% to the original minter
50% to artist (me)

Press '2' to '4' to generate increasingly higher resolutions of the artwork
(will take a while to load, but works)

Press 's' to save a png

Details:

230 hand-picked colour pallets
4 Entity Types
4 Entity Moods
4 Evolution States
3 Types of Defect
2 Bugs

metadata.name: Sketch Block #35
metadata.description:
At the heart of "Sketch Block" is the concept of the sketch block itself - a blank canvas where the possibilities for creation are endless. The name "Sketch Block" reflects the process of creation that inspired the token's design. Like an artist's sketchbook, the token captures the playful experimentation and exploration that underlies the creative process.

The hand-drawn style gives a playful feel to the project, with each shape looking as if it was quickly drawn onto the canvas. Along with the use of vibrant color palettes with tones ranging from soft pastels to bold and bright tones, the projects can produce a wide range of different results.


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

User Controls:

- Press 'h' to save the image

metadata.name: Inner Chaos #123
metadata.description:
Inner Chaos is about my personal struggles with anxiety and fear. Through this artwork, I attempt to visually represent the complex and often overwhelming emotions that I experience on a daily basis. It is a reflection of the cyclical nature of my thoughts and feelings, and the ways in which I try to make sense of them. But as I delve deeper into my own personal experiences, I realize that in the end, internal chaos should not be controlled, but accepted.

This artwork is my most personal, as it reflects my innermost sensations. It is a reminder to myself and to others that it is okay to not have everything under control, and that it is important to allow the uncertainty and unpredictability of life. I hope that it will resonate with others and provide a sense of connection and understanding. It is a reminder that we are not alone in our struggles and that it is important to embrace our own imperfections.


Please use fullscreen or download artwork in high resolution for a better viewing experience. Chrome is highly recommended for high res saving.

Made with love and p5js.


Controls in fullscreen:
[1] - save PNG 1200 x 1800
[2] - save PNG 2400 x 3600
[3] - save PNG 4800 x 7200
[4] - save PNG 7200 x 10800

On mobile:
[quick tap] - save PNG

metadata.name: Abstract Comic #72
metadata.description:
Comics were the trigger for my first absolute rapture. It was so intense that I couldn't wait to get home from school to dive into my secret box of comics and, for a few hours, escape to the world of superheroes. And, at least for a short time, be taken away from reality in which I was ostracized from society at school only because I liked math, and because I thought Spiderman and Batman were cool.

Decades later, the only thing that can be compared to the appearance of comics is the discovery of generative art. I haven't felt such a boyish trance since the appearance of the comics. And nothing has come more naturally than trying to unite my two loves.

This piece tries to achieve a comic vibe using abstract shapes and tries to convey the texture of the paper, which was of poor quality but had the most beautiful smell in the world. It was a challenge to create dynamics, action, movement, fight, and childlike joy all at the same time. Each color palette is inspired by some of the most famous comic book heroes and villains. But by far the biggest challenge was making this piece a direct link to childhood for all of you.

I sincerely hope that I succeeded.


Options:

- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 'd' to save a hi-res PNG image

Created using p5.js
Bajiru, January 2023.

metadata.name: Sands of Time #318
metadata.description:
We've been recently inspired to do this work while being on vacation, in one the most vibrant cities in the world, in the hot pot and intermixture of cultures, terrains and soundscapes. Borrowing the metaphors of sand, from Negarestani's "Cyclonopedia", and of time from "Chronosis", these living substances, we wanted to represent some of the vibes, that have been implanted into our gritty enduring nomadic existence.

This work was created to celebrate #fxhashturnsone event.

- #Tezos4Iran

Made with love, AI and p5.js code

November, 2022
Julia V & YulikolaY

metadata.name: Punktwelt #87
metadata.description:
Continuing on the theme of color perception in Farbteiler, Punktwelt is an exploration of color interaction, projection and perceived depth, and the aesthetics of simple Boolean operations on form.

Each shape is the result of a single block, a rectangular cuboid, subjected to a series of Boolean subtractions with other blocks, and rendered in parallel projection, oblique or axonometric, in the abstract landscape of the Punktwelt.

Some have horizons, some have banded or striped backgrounds. The unnatural drawing order and chromatic differences of the individual faces sometimes yields illusory or paradoxical visual geometries.

Press ’s’ to save a png. Press ’4’ to export a high resolution png. Press ’8’ to export a very high resolution png. Press ’e’ to export an SVG file (may take some time and produce large files).

Aspect ratio variations are 4:5, 5:4, 2:3, 3:2 and 1:1.

Built in Javascript with p5.js, p5.svg and csg.js.
